This paper is about mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT) and economics (cs.EC). The paper also uses expected utility theory, which is a concept from decision theory and probability theory, making cs.DS a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the use of randomized mechanisms, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
